# Google Photos API Configuration
# To use real community photos from Google Photos, set these environment variables

# Google Photos API Key (get from Google Cloud Console)
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_PHOTOS_API_KEY=your_google_photos_api_key_here

# Community Album IDs (get these from Google Photos shared albums)
NEXT_PUBLIC_IGBO_CARDIFF_ALBUM_ID=album_id_for_igbo_cardiff_community
NEXT_PUBLIC_NIGERIAN_LONDON_ALBUM_ID=album_id_for_nigerian_london_community
NEXT_PUBLIC_GHANAIAN_MANCHESTER_ALBUM_ID=album_id_for_ghanaian_manchester_community

# Fallback album for communities without specific albums
NEXT_PUBLIC_FALLBACK_ALBUM_ID=default_community_album_id

# Instructions for setup:
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console (console.cloud.google.com)
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 3. Enable the Google Photos Library API
# 4. Create credentials (API Key)
# 5. Set up shared albums in Google Photos
# 6. Get the album IDs from the shared album URLs
# 7. Add the values above to your .env.local file